$interpreted: Tindoiimu: Baa Baa, you said your father took you down these roads when you were a kid?
Baa Baa: Once, yeah. So there are some parts I might not remember too clearly. Stick close~
Tindoiimu: (This... these patterns... this was done by hand... is this Qimen Dunjia?)
Baa Baa: At this point you have to move some stone into some specific spot, but... bugger, this map is too old.
Baa Baa: Can't tell which stone is the right one...
Jiyanama: Now don't tell me we'll be trapped here...
Baa Baa: Ah, forget it. No point thinking too much! A stopped clock's right twice a day, eh?
Tindoiimu: Wait, what!? Baa Baa, that could be a trap!
Baa Baa: Whoa! What the!?
Tindoiimu: Hold tight! Don't get swept away!
Jiyanama: He... Help!!
Tindoiimu: Whoa...
Jiyanama: Where are we now? I can't see a thing...
Jiyanama: That sound... what is that sound?
Tindoiimu: Hold on, I think I've heard it before...
Tindoiimu: ...The East... Alliance!
Jiyanama: Don't kill us! Please, we're people too!
Tindoiimu: ...Stone?
Tindoiimu: (Could it be... this is some kind of test?)
Tindoiimu: (If you look closely, these soldiers' movements keep repeating. Their path is the same, too...)
Jiyanama: Please, I surrender! I surrender!!
Jiyanama: Don't kill me! Spare my life, please!!
Tindoiimu: Nana, stay where you are!
Jiyanama: Huh?
Tindoiimu: Look, their movements are fixed! These soldiers are circling something...
Tindoiimu: In the center... the Alliance's proudest moment. When the Insect king offered up his daughter as a political hostage...
Tindoiimu: —I've done what you've asked! Destroy it!
Jiyanama: They're... statues? It's all so realistic...
Tindoiimu: Look at all this water. That must be the sound I heard—like a waterfall, mixed with the sound of marching.
Tindoiimu: I know what this is... it's the Waterfall of Illusion.
Jiyanama: But how? Isn't this the Qilin Tribe's sacred land?
Jiyanama: I've heard this place is terrible. Even for fierce qilin warriors—most who attempt to pass through are killed... What are we going to do!?
Tindoiimu: ...Those who must come, will come...
Tindoiimu: Let's go.
